  "text": "Circular No. 505/01/2000-CX F.NO. 209/55/99-CX.6 Government of India Ministry of Finance Department of Revenue Central Board of Excise & Customs New Delhi, the 3, Jan. 2000 Subject: Warehousing --- all automobile manufacturers covered It is directed to enclose CBEC Order number 1/2000-Central Excise dated 3 rd January, 2000 whereby \"All automobiles manufacturers who have signed Memorandum of Understanding with DGFT\" has been specified as class of exporters for the purpose of notification number 26/98-CE(N.T.) dated 15 th July, 1998. The procedure specified in Board's Circular No. 422/55/98-CX dated 21 st September, 1998 shall be followed in this regard. 2. The trade and the field formations may suitably be informed. -- 1 of 1 --",
